column1: Baby Barnaby's////Definitely pretty good food. Came here on a Friday morning for breakfast and it wasn't too busy. I had the apple pecan pancakes and really liked them. They weren't too sweet and the apples on the bottom was a nice treat! My dad ordered the green eggs
column2: which were also solid though the sausage was a bit salty. And my mom had the lox bagels
column3: but the we found the smoked salmon a bit too salty as well.
